The paper deals with game theory and optimization problems in the context of multi-battle contests with budget constraints. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves decision-making and strategic planning, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of dynamic programming algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with auctions and economic mechanisms, which are relevant to cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
